insertAirportProperty

boolean insertAirportProperty(int id,
                              String key,
                              String value)
                              throws SQLException
Adds a property to an airport.

Both key and value strings are converted to constants. If the value string can be parsed as an integer, it is not converted.

Parameters:
id - Airport id
key - Property key
value - Property value.
Returns:
true if value was converted to a constant, false otherwise.
Throws:
SQLException

insertAirspaceArc

                       int maxLat,
                       int minLng,
                       int maxLng,
                       int startAngle,
                       int sweepAngle)
                       throws SQLException
Adds an arc to an airspace shape.

Parameters:
id - Airspace id.
num - Sequence number of arc.
minLat - Minimum latitude of the circle containing the arc, in E6 format
maxLat - Maximum latitude of the circle containing the arc, in E6 format
minLng - Minimum longitude of the circle containing the arc, in E6 format
maxLng - Maximum longitude of the circle containing the arc, in E6 format
startAngle - Starting angle (in degrees E6) clockwise from East
sweepAngle - Sweep angle (in degrees E6) measured clockwise.

SQLException
